# Appendix P — SLAT for notebooks and interactive docs

An interactive notebook is a document you can read AND run. The runtime
Scheme books are already this — every chapter's Scheme block can run
in the in-page interpreter (Lane 10 renderer). This appendix
formalizes the notebook record.

## The notebook record

```motoi-scheme
(notebook
  :id        \"nb-tulip-analysis-2026-07-12\"
  :author    'alfred
  :title     \"Why the tulip brooch keeps selling out\"
  :cells     ((cell :kind 'prose
                    :body \"Started noticing the tulip goes fast every spring.\")
              (cell :kind 'scheme
                    :body \"(sales-of 'tulip-brooch :range 'ytd)\"
                    :result \"(sales :units 342 :revenue 15390)\")
              (cell :kind 'chart
                    :body \"(chart :weekly-sales 'tulip-brooch)\"
                    :result-path \"chart-2026-07-12-tulip.svg\")
              (cell :kind 'prose
                    :body \"Peak is in early April. Prep more inventory.\"))
  :saved-at  #inst \"2026-07-12T15:00:00Z\"
  :outcome   'insight-recorded)
```

Head: `notebook`. Positional not used. Cells are ordered.

## Cell kinds

- **prose** — Markdown-formatted text.
- **scheme** — a Motoi Scheme block, runnable inline.
- **chart** — a chart cell (Scheme-generated).
- **table** — a table cell (from a Scheme value).
- **image** — an image reference (from URL or local).
- **question** — a question the operator wants the runtime to answer.

## The `question` cell — the runtime in the notebook

```motoi-scheme
(cell :kind 'question
      :body \"Why did the tulip brooch spike last April?\"
      :motoi-answer
        (cell :kind 'prose
              :body \"Looking at the data: (a) Mother's Day approach
                     drove searches up 3.4x; (b) an Etsy trending
                     feature amplified it; (c) two influencer posts
                     coincided. All three are seasonal — expect a
                     repeat this April.\"
              :sources '(\"etsy-trends-2026-04\"
                         \"influencer-post-a\"
                         \"influencer-post-b\")))
```

The question cell holds both the ask and the runtime's answer. She can
answer notebook questions from her sidecar + the operator's data.

## Notebook execution model

- Cells run in order.
- Each cell can reference earlier cells' results (`(cell-result :n 2)`).
- The whole notebook is a single fuel budget.
- Failure halts execution + records the failure cell.

```motoi-scheme
(notebook-run
  :notebook-id \"nb-tulip-analysis-2026-07-12\"
  :started     #inst \"2026-07-12T15:00:00Z\"
  :fuel-used   1200
  :cells-ran   4
  :cells-failed 0
  :outcome     'complete)
```

## Notebooks as training material

Sealed notebooks are training-relevant. They pair operator questions
with the runtime's grounded answers. Great LIMA-tier material.

```motoi-scheme
(training-candidate
  :from        'notebook
  :notebook-id \"nb-tulip-analysis-2026-07-12\"
  :suitable-as '(question-answer-pair reasoning-example)
  :quality     'high)
```

## The book renderer as a notebook

Every book chapter, in the Lane 10 renderer, IS a notebook. The
prose cells are the chapter body; the Scheme cells are the runnable
`prose-with-scheme` records. Same shape.

